pullRequest.bodyText:
I wanted to remove those many lines of MM log coming from the hexTileset and the MekSummary cache, so I changed it all to use the MMLogger and set them to Info and the log level to Warning.
The calls to MMLogger are very bulky (certainly worse than //NON-NLS1) so I added some convenience functions. These only need a this as the first parameter (instead of getClass()) and don't need the method name which is taken from the stack trace instead. There's also a convenience function for setting the log level that uses this as a parameter instead of a String giving the class name, removing the chance to misspell and not notice.
Together with the constants
private static final MMLogger LOG = DefaultMmLogger.getInstance();
private static final LogLevel LOGLVL = LogLevel.WARNING;

one can call
LOG.info(this, "Unable to load wreck image for entity: " + entity.getShortNameRaw());
and
LOG.setLogLevel(this, LOGLVL);
which I think is an improvement.

